Although the alternative form clearly shows only three strokes, it is still counted as four strokes when using a Chinese dictionary. Compare [[氵]] from {{term|水||water|sc=Hani}}, [[扌]] from {{term|手||hand|sc=Hani}}, and [[忄]] from {{term|心||heart|sc=Hani}}, all of which are a 3-stroke form from a 4-stroke character.

===Etymology===
{{liushu|p}} – the dot is the ear. In the form {{Hani|[[犭]]}}, a dog that is up on its hind legs.

